s=title> Re: OT- Another School Shooting</span><hr size=1> Sure, it may not be the fault of this guy's parents that he went in and killed people, but it is a well known fact that the disintegration of the morals, respect, and coping abilities are a direct result of a few main factors, the most important of which is parental participation in their children's lives and good discipline. Effective discipline is lacking in most children's lives. They lack structure. While to some corporal punishment may not seem the answer, there is the undeniable fact that since it has been all but outlawed in any form, the youth of today have gotten more out of control. They don't have the same respect for their fellow students, authority, or themselves. They don't have a clear sense about the consequences of their actions.<br>
<br>
Before I get flamed to holy hell and back over saying this, I am also going to add this: Way to go! to those parents who are actively trying to make their children better people, showing interest and support in their children's lives, leading them by being a good example. People today are busy, and it's easier to let the kids do their own thing, but while its easier, it is NOT the best thing for them. Kids need structure, discipline, support and goals to grow up well adjusted. Lacking any of these, their coping abilities are compromised, even in the best of kids, and if there are emotional of behavioral problems, this just increases. <br>
<br>
People in general need to be on the lookout for kids in need of a kind word, a word of encouragement, constructive feedback. Every little bit helps. When things like this happen, it is a sign of society deteriorating one piece at a time, and that is where we need to focus to fix it. Placing micro blame is no way to address and help a macro problem.<br>
<br>
By the way, I favor intellectual discipline and deprivement as a reward for negative behavior, but there are extreme cases and situations when a warmed butt gets attention more than anything else can. I haven't been spanked since I was 8. Why? I figured out what caused it and stopped doing f*cked up sh*t. I don't condone physical abuse, but I know the difference, and I think people just waiting to be the hero of some little boy getting his butt smacked because he is cussing at his mother in the grocery store are worthless. <br>
<br>
Now that I am kinda getting off topic.../rant off. <p><BR><center>
